article.headline: Centenary 91, Texas State 85
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Larry Logan scored 20 points and was one of five Centenary players in double figures as the Gents defeated Texas State 91-85 on Tuesday night. Alexander Starr added 17 points, Nick Stallings 16, Lance Hill 13 and Tyrone Hamilton 12 for Centenary (1-1). The Gents hit 60 percent (33-of-55) of its field goals of their field goals for the game. Hamilton had a game-high 6 assists. Charles Dotson led Texas State (1-1) with 20 points, hitting 8-of-15 shots. Brandon Bush and Brent Holder each added 15. Brandon Thomas had 10 points and had a game-high 10 rebounds. The Bobcats hit 28-of-64 of their field goals. Centenary led 48-32 at the halftime and staved off a Texas State rally in the second half. The Bobcats held a 42-27 advantage in rebounds and hit 7-of-16 3-pointers. But they trailed in assists, 20-10, and turned the ball over 26 times to the Gents' 20.
